# Business Problems

## BP-01
Declining customer retention due to customers switching to competitors.

## BP-02
High stock-out rate resulting in customer dissatisfaction and revenue loss.

## BP-03
High order cancellation rate impacting customer trust and operational efficiency.

## BP-04
High checkout abandonment leads to lost revenue.

## BP-05
Delayed deliveries affecting customer satisfaction and brand perception.

## BP-06
Poor visibility into operational KPIs, delays business decision-making.

# Hypotheses

## BP-01: Declining Customer Retention

Possible hypotheses:

1. Late deliveries.
2. Wrong product deliveries.
3. Product stock-outs.
4. Poor checkout experience.
5. Hidden platform fees and pricing transparency issues.
6. Customers perceive competitors as offering better value.
7. Poor customer support experience.
8. Poor delivery partner experience.
9. Lack of loyalty benefits.
10. Weak brand perception.
11. Validate whether customer retention has actually declined before proceeding with root cause analysis.

## BP-07
Low product discovery resulting in reduced conversion and lower average order value.
